## 3. Critical Architecture Mandates (MUST FOLLOW)

🚨 **DO NOT DEVIATE FROM THESE RULES:**

### ❌ No Monolithic HTML
*   **Problem:** Hardcoding player profiles (e.g., a static Shohei Ohtani block) kills scalability.
*   **Mandate:** Use a **JS-driven UI**. The `#prof-content` container should be empty on load and populated dynamically.

```javascript
// ✅ CORRECT: Dynamic Rendering
function renderPlayerProfile(model) {
  const root = document.getElementById('prof-content');
  root.innerHTML = `
    <div class="profile-layout">
      ${renderProfileHeader(model)}
      <div class="center-panel">
        ${renderKPIs(model)}
        <div id="pp-bars"></div>
      </div>
      ${renderProfileRightColumn(model)}
    </div>
  `;
  renderPercentilesGrouped('pp-bars', model.grouped);
}
```

### ❌ No Inline Styles
*   **Problem:** `<div style="font-family:Bebas Neue; font-size:20px">` is unmaintainable.
*   **Mandate:** Use CSS classes for everything.

```css
/* ✅ CORRECT: CSS Classes */
.title-xl {
  font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif;
  font-size: 24px;
  letter-spacing: 2px;
  color: var(--text-primary);
}
```

### ❌ No Fabricated Data
*   **Mandate:** If data is missing, show "—". **DO NOT** guess, simulate, or fill with averages.

