## 5. Analytics Philosophy & Percentile Engine

### 1) Percentiles are Primary UI
The system prefers **Percentiles > Raw Stats**. All key metrics must be expressed as a percentile (0–100) with color-coded meaning.

### 2) Direction Matters (Inversion)
Some metrics invert (e.g., **K%**, **Chase%**, **Whiff%** are better when **LOW**). The engine must handle this:

```javascript
// ✅ Direction-Aware Percentile Engine
function computePercentile(arr, val, higherBetter) {
  if (val == null) return null;
  const clean = arr.filter(x => x != null && isFinite(x)).sort((a, b) => a - b);
  if (clean.length < 10) return null;

  let idx = clean.findIndex(v => v >= val);
  if (idx < 0) idx = clean.length - 1;

  let pct = Math.round((idx / clean.length) * 100);
  if (!higherBetter) pct = 100 - pct;

  return Math.max(1, Math.min(99, pct)); // Clamp 1-99
}
```

