## 6. UI / Visual System Rules (STRICT SPEC)

### 1) Percentile Bars (The "Savant" Spec)
Each bar must follow this exact structure:
*   **Track:** Light gray background.
*   **Fill:** Colored based on value.
*   **Bubble:** A circle (~22px) containing the percentile number, sitting **ON** the fill edge.

```css
/* ✅ Percentile Bar CSS */
.pct-row {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 110px 1fr 60px;
  gap: 10px;
  align-items: center;
  padding: 6px 0;
}
.pct-track {
  position: relative;
  height: 18px;
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, .1);
  border-radius: 10px;
}
.pct-fill {
  height: 100%;
  border-radius: 10px;
  transition: width .6s ease;
}
.pct-bubble {
  position: absolute;
  top: 50%;
  transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
  width: 22px;
  height: 22px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  font-size: 11px;
}
```

### 2) Color = Meaning
*   **Red (≥ 80):** Elite / Exploit
*   **Orange (60-79):** Above Average
*   **Gray (40-59):** Average
*   **Blue (20-39):** Below Average
*   **Dark Blue (< 20):** Poor

